  <title><em>ISCAM</em> Chapter 5 Intro</title>

  <introduction>
  <title>COMPARING SEVERAL POPULATIONS, EXPLORING RELATIONSHIPS</title>
    <p>The idea of comparisons has been a recurring theme throughout this course. In previous chapters, you were limited to exploring only one or two groups at a time. In this chapter, you extend those ideas to multiple groups and to relationships between variables.</p>
    <p><alert>Section 1: Two Categorical Variables</alert></p>
    <ul>
      <li><p><xref ref="inv-5-1" text="custom">Investigation 5.1: Dr. Spock's Trial</xref> - Chi-squared test for homogeneity of proportions</p></li>
      <li><p><xref ref="inv-5-1a" text="custom">Investigation 5.1A: Newspaper Credibility Decline</xref> - Comparing distributions</p></li>
      <li><p><xref ref="inv-5-2" text="custom">Investigation 5.2: A moral tale</xref> - Randomized experiment</p></li>
      <li><p><xref ref="inv-5-3" text="custom">Investigation 5.3: Nightlights and Near sightedness (cont.)</xref> - Chi-squared test for association</p></li>
      <li><p><xref ref="section5-1-summary" text="custom">Section 5.1 Summary</xref></p></li>
    </ul>
    <p><alert>Section 2: Comparing Several Population Means</alert></p>
    <ul>
      <li><p><xref ref="inv-5-4" text="custom">Investigation 5.4: Disability discrimination</xref> - Reasoning of ANOVA</p></li>
      <li><p><xref ref="inv-5-5" text="custom">Investigation 5.5: Restaurant spending and music</xref> - ANOVA practice</p></li>
      <li><p><xref ref="inv-5-5" text="custom">Applet Exploration</xref></p></li>
      <li><p><xref ref="section5-2-summary" text="custom">Section 5.2 Summary</xref></p></li>
    </ul>
    <p><alert>Section 3: Two Quantitative Variables</alert></p>
    <ul>
      <li><p><xref ref="inv-5-6" text="custom">Investigation 5.6: Cat jumping</xref> - Scatterplots</p></li>
      <li><p><xref ref="inv-5-7" text="custom">Investigation 5.7: Drive for show, putt for dough</xref> - Correlation coefficient</p></li>
      <li><p><xref ref="inv-5-7" text="custom">Applet Exploration</xref></p></li>
      <li><p><xref ref="inv-5-8" text="custom">Investigation 5.8: Height and foot size</xref> - Least Squares Regression</p></li>
      <li><p><xref ref="inv-5-9" text="custom">Investigation 5.9: Money-making movies</xref> - Application</p></li>
      <li><p><xref ref="section5-3-summary" text="custom">Section 5.3 Summary</xref></p></li>
    </ul>
